{{Quote|We have been the biggest supplier of raw metals and minerals ever since Klegger Corp went bust just before the end of the Clone Wars. Something happened to their main plant...not sure what, but most of it ended up falling into the lava pool. They just never recovered from that incident and we took over.|[[Foreman/Legends|Foreman]] [[Chivos]], about [[Mensix Corp]]|<ref name="SWG:SftM">{{SWGcite|exp=ToOW|type=general|Supplies for the Miners|Mustafar}}</ref>}}
The '''Klegger Corporation''', also known simply as '''Klegger Corp.''', was a [[Mining/Legends|mining]] corporation that exploited the natural resources of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Mustafar/Legends|Mustafar]] until the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

==Description==
[[File:KleggerCorpMiningFacility.png|left|250px|thumb|The Klegger Corp Mining Facility during the Clone Wars]]
Klegger Corporation was a [[Mining/Legends|mining]] company<ref name="SWG:MMF" /> that mined the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Mustafar/Legends|Mustafar]] on the behalf of the [[Techno Union/Legends|Techno Union]], a commerce guild of which Klegger Corp was a subsidiary.<ref name="FF2" /> The company was based in the massive [[Klegger Corp Mining Facility/Legends|Klegger Corp Mining Facility]].<ref name="SWG:MMF" />

The mining operations of Klegger Corp. consisted of collecting a huge amount of [[Magma/Legends|lava]] in order to extract the valuable [[Ore/Legends|ore]] contained in the magma. The Klegger Corp Mining Facility used electromagnetic and [[Tractor beam/Legends|tractor beam]] extraction technologies to collect liquid ores that were then treated in a giant centrifuge to extract the ore from the lava. The facility also processed lava manually collected by native [[Mustafarian/Legends|Mustafarians]] and [[Mining droid/Legends|mining droids]].<ref name="SWCL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2005)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> The miners used various tools and technology, such as [[Lava skimmer/Legends|lava skimmers]] and [[Lava skiff/Legends|lava skiffs]], as well as droids, including [[Mustafar panning droid|panning droids]], [[DLC-13 Mining Droid|DLC-13 mining droids]] and [[Mining Droid MK3|MK3 mining droids]].<ref name="RotS">{{Film|III}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|If this contract fails, the entire company fails. All of these people will be out of work and I am not so sure that anyone will come back to pick up the pieces like we did with Klegger.|[[Milo Mensix]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:TDS">{{SWGcite|exp=ToOW|type=general|The Downed Ship|Mustafar}}</ref>}}
The Klegger Corporation began to mine Mustafar after the Techno Union took control of the planet around [[300 BBY/Legends|300 BBY]].<ref name="FF2" /> It then became the dominant mining company on Mustafar.<ref name="SWG:TCFM">{{SWGcite|exp=ToOW|type=general|The Crystal Flats Markers|Mustafar}}</ref>

In [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]],<ref name="TNEC" /> at the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the [[Separatist Council/Legends|Separatist Council]] relocated to the planet Mustafar and used the Klegger Corp Mining Facility as its headquarters. The Clone Wars ended when [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] [[Mission to Mustafar/Legends|slaughtered]] the entire Council in Klegger Corp's mining facility. A short time later, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] arrived on Mustafar and [[Duel on Mustafar|dueled]] and defeated his former apprentice. The Klegger Corp Mining Facility was severely damaged during the confrontation, and a part of its structure collapsed into the surrounding lava.<ref name="RotS" /> Klegger Corp. never recovered from that destruction of its main facility;<ref name="SWG:SftM" /> the incident left the company bankrupt.<ref name="SWG:MMF" />

After the Clone Wars, the Mustafarians took over the mining operations of the Techno Union.<ref name="FF2" /> [[Milo Mensix]], a local corporation executive, salvaged the assets and the staff of Klegger Corp, preventing the mining business from falling apart.<ref name="SWG:TDS" /> [[Mensix Corp]] eventually became the largest mining corporation on the planet.<ref name="SWG:MMF" />

